cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.CYBER, cs.NI

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on analyzing human mobility through a social perspective and investigates the impact of social groups in mobility patterns.
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a likely category as the findings can be used to propose meeting prediction algorithms, opportunistic routing and information diffusion protocols.
- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is another possible category as the paper analyzes social groups and their dynamics.
- cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy) is a potential category as the paper uses the MIT Reality Mining proximity trace dataset, which may involve privacy and security concerns.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is another possible category as the paper proposes protocols and applications that can take advantage of the revealed properties of group mobility patterns.
